news.title: Ulhasnagar: Building declared 'dangerous', yet five flats were occupied
news.para: Over the past 12 years, 38 buildings in Ulhasnagar have collapsed, some partially, killing 42 people and leaving at least 5,000 homeless.

news.title: UP RERA imposes penalty against 13 developers
news.para: The authority is making constant efforts to ensure enforcement of its orders and provide speedy justice to the aggrieved allottees. The action of penalty against the guilty promoters is an important step towards compelling them to comply with the orders of the authority.

news.title: Come clean on regularisation anomalies: VB notice to Ludhiana civic body
news.para: Even after receiving six letters from the vigilance office, the MC officials had not submitted the action taken report. Therefore, one final letter has been now issued by the vigilance department.

news.title: BDA, BBMP buildings on SWD will also be demolished: Karnataka revenue minister
news.para: The revenue minister and CM both added that the BDA properties, which are going to be constructed in the future, will also be taken into account for not encroaching on SWDs.

news.title: Maharashtra government focuses on e-registration of properties
news.para: More realtors registered with Maharashtra Real Estate Regulatory Authority (MahaRERA) would soon get the software following due checks, a senior property registration official said on Thursday.

news.title: Birla group's RCCPL gets clearance for limestone mining in Tiger Reserves
news.para: The cement plant has been diverted 467.45 hectares of reserve forest land in the tiger corridor for dolomite/limestone mining in three compartments falling in Hirapur, Govindpur and Pimparwadi in Pandharkawda division under Yavatmal Circle.

news.title: Kochi: P&T Colony rehabilitation project misses yet another deadline
news.para: ​​The project had already missed at least a dozen deadlines and GCDA, which implements the project, said that the new deadline will be by October last week.

news.title: Gujarat: Talatis can issue legal heir certificates for flats
news.para: After the talati issues this certificate and the mamlatdar ratifies it, the local district court issues a succession certificate. Since 2014, the revenue department has allowed talatis to issue legal heir certificates only in case of agricultural or non-agricultural land.

news.title: SC directs Noida authority to allot flats to 844 plot owners
news.para: ​A bench of Chief Justice U U Lalit and Justices Indira Banerjee and KM Joseph noted that New Okhla Industrial Authority (NOIDA) is agreeable to re-lay part of Sector 43 and to make allotments of multi-storeyed flats in favour of 844 persons; with each of those flats admeasuring about 1800 square feet.

news.title: Chandigarh housing board lists flat transfer guidelines
news.para: ​​The flat should be free from all litigation, building violation, maintenance issues, etc. All dues should have been paid.

news.title: Delhi: NOC not needed for properties that became freehold before March 2000
news.para: L&DO, which comes under the Union housing and urban affairs ministry, had in July issued directions to the Delhi revenue department, asking not to register any property without the NOC.

news.title: Sebi permits REITs, InvITs to issue commercial papers
news.para: The move came after Reserve Bank Commercial Paper Directions last month indicated that InvIT and REIT having net worth of at least Rs 100 crore are eligible to issue commercial paper.

news.title: Blackstone's Nucleus Office Parks leases 7.5 lakh sq ft with Rs 1,100 crore annual rent
news.para: The operating platform has completed fresh office projects spread over nearly 2.5 million sq ft across its developments including in Mumbai’s Lower Parel, Bangalore’s Outer Ring Road (ORR) and Gurgaon, taking its total portfolio size to over 22 million sq ft.

news.title: No GST on sale of plots with basic infrastructure: AAR
news.para: It was always clear that land is not subject to GST. However, an endless bout of litigation arose on whether sale of plots when some basic development has been carried out is subject to GST. This litigation is now easing.

news.title: ED attaches Rs 147-crore assets of Gupta Builders and Promoters in cheating case
news.para: ​​The attached properties include commercial spaces, residential houses, agriculture lands and bank accounts belonging to Gupta Builders and Promoters Pvt Ltd (GBPPL), its directors Satish Gupta, Pardeep Gupta and their associates Anupam Gupta and Navraj Mittal, the ED said in a statement.
